part.name: body
part.text: To delete messages, you'll need to use the app or service where they're stored. Here are some examples:​ WhatsApp:​ Open the chat, tap and hold the message, then tap "Delete for Everyone."​Google Voice:​ Open the Voice app, tap "Messages," tap the conversation, tap and hold the message, then tap "Delete."​iPhone Messages:​ Open the Messages app, swipe left on the conversation, then tap "Delete."​Facebook Messenger:​ Open the Messenger app, tap the conversation, tap and hold the message, then tap "Delete."​ If you're unsure how to delete messages in a specific app or service, search for instructions online or contact the app's support team.​
